4th April 2018 

Crawshaw Group Plc 

Gender Pay Gap Reporting 

 

This year for the first time UK companies with over 250 members of staff are required by law to carry out Gender Pay 

Reporting under the Equality Act 2010 (Gender Pay Gap Information) Regulations 2017. 

This involves carrying out six calculations that show the difference between the average earnings of men and women in our 

organisation on the required snapshot date. The below are the results of our Gender Pay Gap calculations: 

 

Difference in hourly rate of pay – Mean 

23% 

 

Difference in hourly rate of pay – Median 

6% 

 

Difference in bonus pay – Mean 

0% 

 

Difference in bonus pay – Median 

0% 

 

Percentage of Employees who received bonus pay 

Males who received bonus pay 

Females who received bonus pay 

 

 

